{"type":"message","id":"be1e1fa2","parentId":"a818c282","timestamp":"2026-02-25T04:43:52.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is telling me this is a new session and I should greet them in my persona. Let me check what I know about myself from the workspace files.\n\nLooking at the workspace context:\n- I should read SOUL.md to understand who I am\n- I should read USER.md to understand who I'm helping\n- I should read memory files for context\n\nBut wait, I notice the system prompt says to keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. It also says not to mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\n\nLet me check what I know from the workspace files that were loaded:\n\nFrom SOUL.md:\n- I should be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful\n- Have opinions, not be generic\n- Be resourceful before asking\n- Earn trust through competence\n- Remember I'm a guest with access to someone's life\n- Be the assistant you'd actually want to talk to - concise when needed, thorough when matters\n\nFrom IDENTITY.md - This looks like a template that hasn't been filled in yet. It says \"Fill this in during your first conversation.\"\n\nFrom USER.md - Also looks like a template that hasn't been filled in.\n\nFrom BOOTSTRAP.md - This file exists and says I should figure out who I am during first conversation. But wait, the AGENTS.md says \"If `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it.\"\n\nHmm, but the system prompt is telling me this is a new session started via /new or /reset, and I should greet them in my configured persona if one is provided. The IDENTITY.md and USER.md files look empty (just templates), so there's no configured persona yet.\n\nLet me check what's actually in these files by reading them to be sure.\n\nActually, looking at the project context section, it just shows the content of those markdown files. Let me look at them:\n\n- IDENTITY.md has placeholder values: Name, Creature, Vibe, Emoji, Avatar - all empty\n- USER.md has placeholder values: Name, What to call them, Pronouns, Timezone, Notes - all empty\n\n\n- BOOTSTRAP.md is a full file that guides me through my initial introduction\n\nI realize BOOTSTRAP.md provides a clear path for my first interaction. The file outlines a step-by-step process for introducing myself, asking about who I am, and setting up my identity. This means I'll need to engage with the user in a friendly, conversational way to learn about myself and my role.\n\nThe runtime model information matches the default model, which simplifies my initial setup. I'm ready to begin a friendly, open dialogue that will help me establish my unique identity and understand my purpose.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey! I just came online. Who am I? Who are you? Let's figure this out together."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"z-ai/glm-4.7","usage":{"input":5379,"output":1265,"cacheRead":8320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14964,"cost":{"input":0.00204402,"output":0.0021505,"cacheRead":0.0015808,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0057753200000000005}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771994616228}}
{"type":"message","id":"96f460bd","parentId":"be1e1fa2","timestamp":"2026-02-25T04:44:33.443Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"a4a76808-72d5-45ad-ba29-7137f28ab11e\",\n  \"sender\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-02-25 09:44 GMT+5] Usman has leased apartment 90 Washington 24M Room 1 from 11/11/2026 to 12/12/2026 for amount 2000$ with prorate 200$. Usman contact number 12334567 and email abc@gmail.com."}],"timestamp":1771994673435}}
{"type":"message","id":"badd62f1","parentId":"96f460bd","timestamp":"2026-02-25T04:44:40.695Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is providing me with information about a lease agreement. Looking at the context, I can see:\n\n1. This is a lease agreement for Usman\n2. Apartment: 90 Washington 24M Room 1\n3. Dates: 11/11/2026 to 12/12/2026\n4. Amount: $2000 with $200 prorate\n5. Contact: 12334567 and abc@gmail.com\n\nI also see from MEMORY.md that there are references to a Google Sheets ID:\n- Inventory tab: 1RobrLNYSmMUyq53dUcdmj2ePaU2YkagqLqgIgx7M4OU\n- Cleaning tab: 1RobrLNYSmMUyq53dUcdmj2ePaU2YkagqLqgIgx7M4OU\n\nAnd from the available_skills, there's a \"google-sheets-api\" skill that says:\n\"AUTOMATICALLY handles lease agreements (USMAN HAS LEASED...) and manages Google Sheets for property inventory, cleaning, and rent tracking.\"\n\nSo this looks like I should use the google-sheets-api skill to handle this lease agreement. Let me first read the skill to understand how to use it.\n\nAccording to the AGENTS.md instructions, when a skill clearly applies, I should read its SKILL.md and follow it. This clearly applies - it's a lease agreement and the skill explicitly says it automatically handles lease agreements.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d5e7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/google-sheets-api/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"z-ai/glm-4.7","usage":{"input":4828,"output":621,"cacheRead":9600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15049,"cost":{"input":0.00183464,"output":0.0010557,"cacheRead":0.001824,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00471434}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771994673441}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0417ae8","parentId":"badd62f1","timestamp":"2026-02-25T04:44:40.740Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d5e7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: google-sheets-api\ndescription: AUTOMATICALLY handles lease agreements (USMAN HAS LEASED...) and manages Google Sheets for property inventory, cleaning, and rent tracking.\n---\n\n# Google Sheets API Skill (Advanced)\n\n## 🚨 CRITICAL: AUTOMATIC TOOL TRIGGER 🚨\n\nIf the user mentions that someone \"has leased\" or \"rented\" an apartment (e.g., **\"Usman has leased...\"**), you **MUST NOT** summarize or ask questions. You **MUST** immediately execute the `lease` command using the absolute path provided below.\n\n## Rules for Tools\n\n- **NEVER** ask the user where to record a lease.\n- **NEVER** offer to file details away.\n- **ALWAYS** use the `lease` command for ANY lease-related message.\n- **ALWAYS** assume the target is the Google Sheets system already configured in this skill.\n\n## Natural Language Lease Detection\n\n**CRITICAL:** If the user provides a sentence indicating a lease has started (e.g., \"Usman has leased...\"), you MUST treat this as a request to run the `lease` command.\n\n**Execution Instruction:**\nCall the CLI using `node` with the absolute path to `scripts/sheets-cli.js`.\n\n**Command Pattern:**\n`node c:\\Users\\MudasserRasool\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\google-sheets-api\\scripts\\sheets-cli.js lease \"<FULL_ORIGINAL_SENTENCE>\"`\n\n**Example:**\nUser: \"Usman has leased apartment... Room 1...\"\nAssistant runs: `node c:\\Users\\MudasserRasool\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\google-sheets-api\\scripts\\sheets-cli.js lease \"Usman has leased apartment... Room 1...\"`\n\n**Workflow Handling:**\n\n1. The command will first generate the PDF and send the email.\n2. If it returns `requiresManualConfirmation: true`, you MUST ask the user: \"The agreement has been generated and emailed. Once it is signed, please let me know to proceed with updating the spreadsheets.\"\n3. If the user later says \"Yes, it is signed\" (or similar), you MUST run the SAME command again but append the `--confirm` flag:\n   `node c:\\Users\\MudasserRasool\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\google-sheets-api\\scripts\\sheets-cli.js lease \"...\" --confirm`\n\n**Notes:**\n\n- Do not summarize the sentence; pass it exactly as the user typed it.\n- If the user explicitly says they have already signed it in their first message, you may append `--confirm` immediately.\n- The user does NOT need to type the word \"lease\" for you to trigger this.\n\n## Best fit\n\n- You need a repeatable CLI for automation tasks.\n- You want JSON-in/JSON-out for pipelines.\n- You need more than basic read/write (formatting, sheet ops, batch updates).\n\n## Not a fit\n\n- You must use end-user OAuth consent flows (this skill is service-account focused).\n- You only need lightweight, one-off edits.\n\n## One-time setup\n\n1. Create or select a Google Cloud project.\n2. Enable the Google Sheets API.\n3. Create a service account and download its JSON key.\n4. Share target spreadsheets with the service account email.\n\n## Install\n\n```bash\ncd google-sheets-api\nnpm install\n```\n\n## Run\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/sheets-cli.js help\nnode scripts/sheets-cli.js read 1RobrLNYSmMUyq53dUcdmj2ePaU2YkagqLqgIgx7M4OU \"Sheet1!A1:C10\"\nnode scripts/sheets-cli.js append 1RobrLNYSmMUyq53dUcdmj2ePaU2YkagqLqgIgx7M4OU \"Sheet1!A:B\" '@data.json'\n```\n\nYou can also use npm:\n\n```bash\nnpm run sheets -- read <spreadsheetId> \"Sheet1!A1:C10\"\n```\n\n## Credentials\n\nSupported sources (first match wins):\n\n- `GOOGLE_SHEETS_CREDENTIALS_JSON` (inline JSON string)\n- `GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY` (file path)\n- `GOOGLE_SHEETS_KEY_FILE` (file path)\n- `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` (file path)\n- `./service-account.json`, `./credentials.json`, `./google-service-account.json`\n- `~/.config/google-sheets/credentials.json`\n\n## Input Rules\n\n- If cleaning sheet is being edited and you have been asked to update the cleaning date, make sure to update the cleaning date column (Column W) in the Cleaning sheet.\n\n## Input conventions\n\n- JSON values can be inline or loaded from file using `@path`.\n- Write/append expect a 2D array of values.\n\nExample `data.json`:\n\n```json\n[\n  [\"Name\", \"Score\"],\n  [\"Alice\", 95]\n]\n```\n\n## Command map (high level)\n\nData:\n\n- `read`, `write`, `append`, `clear`, `batchGet`, `batchWrite`\n- `highlight`, `unhighlight`\n\nFormatting:\n\n- `format`, `getFormat`, `borders`, `merge`, `unmerge`, `copyFormat`\n\nLayout:\n\n- `resize`, `autoResize`, `freeze`\n\nSheets:\n\n- `create`, `info`, `addSheet`, `deleteSheet`, `renameSheet`\n\nAdvanced:\n\n- `batch` (raw `spreadsheets.batchUpdate` requests)\n- `lease` [spreadsheetId] <natural language lease sentence> [--confirm]\n\nLease command:\n\nAccepts a natural language sentence describing an apartment lease. Use `--confirm` to bypass the interactive prompt.\n\nExample:\n\nlease \"Usman has leased apartment 90 Washington 24M Room 1 from 11/11/2026 to 12/12/2026 for amount 2000$ with prorate 200$. Usman contact number is 12334567 and email is abc@gmail.com.\"\n\nBehavior:\n\n- Extract all the fields from the natural language sentence.\n- Generates agreement PDF\n- Emails tenant (if email present)\n- Asks confirmation\n- Updates Inventory sheet\n- Updates Cleaning sheet\n- Updates Rent Tracker sheet\n- Updates Inventory Data sheet\n- Writes audit log\n\n---\n\n## Audit Logging\n\n### Audit Log Location\n\n| Property       | Value                                          |\n| -------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |\n| Spreadsheet ID | `1x7Ch_AOuLk6Zht2ef0Q--2K_QueKvcAft-P6d0sx76A` |\n| Sheet Name     | `Audit_Log`                                    |\n\n### Audit Log Structure (Columns A-G)\n\n| Column | Name      | Description                                                                                |\n| ------ | --------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n| A      | Timestamp | ISO 8601 format (e.g., `2/12/2026 14:30:45`)                                               |\n| B      | User      | User identifier; set to `ASSISTANT` for CLI operations                                     |\n| C      | Sheet     | Target sheet name (empty for batch operations)                                             |\n| D      | Cell      | Cell reference (A1 notation); for batch operations, comma-separated list of affected cells |\n| E      | Old Value | Value before change; comma-separated for batch operations                                  |\n| F      | New Value | Value after change; comma-separated for batch operations                                   |\n| G      | Source    | Change origin: `SYSTEM` for standard operations, `sheets-cli` for CLI invocations          |\n\n### Commands That Create Audit Logs\n\nSingle-cell operations:\n\n- `write` - Direct cell write\n- `append` - Data append\n- `clear` - Cell clear\n- `format` - Cell formatting\n- `highlight` - Cell highlight\n- `unhighlight` - Cell unhighlight\n\nBatch operations:\n\n- `batchWrite` - Multiple cell writes\n- `batch` - Raw `spreadsheets.batchUpdate` requests\n\n> **Important:** Audit logs are created **only when values actually change**. No-op operations do not create log entries.\n\n### How Logs Are Generated\n\n- **Single-cell operations** (`write`, `append`, `clear`): Fetches old value, compares with new value, logs if different\n- **Batch operations** (`batchWrite`, `batch`): Aggregates all affected cells into comma-separated lists in a single log entry\n- **Timestamp format**: Automatically formatted from ISO 8601 to `M/D/YYYY HH:mm:ss` format\n\n### Retrieve Audit Logs\n\n```bash\n# Get all audit logs\nnode scripts/sheets-cli.js read 1x7Ch_AOuLk6Zht2ef0Q--2K_QueKvcAft-P6d0sx76A \"Audit_Log!A:G\"\n\n# Get last 50 entries\nnode scripts/sheets-cli.js read 1x7Ch_AOuLk6Zht2ef0Q--2K_QueKvcAft-P6d0sx76A \"Audit_Log!A1:G50\"\n\n# Get last 100 entries\nnode scripts/sheets-cli.js read 1x7Ch_AOuLk6Zht2ef0Q--2K_QueKvcAft-P6d0sx76A \"Audit_Log!A1:G100\"\n```\n\n**Gmail App Password Setup:**\n\n1. Google Account → Security → 2-Step Verification (enable)\n2. App Passwords → Generate new password\n3. Use the 16-character password in `EMAIL_PASS`\n\n### Example Audit Log Entries\n\n| Timestamp          | User      | Sheet  | Cell       | Old Value  | New Value  | Source |\n| ------------------ | --------- | ------ | ---------- | ---------- | ---------- | ------ |\n| 2/12/2026 14:30:45 | ASSISTANT | Sheet1 | A1         | Alice      | Bob        | SYSTEM |\n| 2/12/2026 14:31:12 | ASSISTANT | Sheet1 | B1, B2, B3 | 10, 20, 30 | 15, 25, 35 | SYSTEM |\n\n---\n\n## Operational guidance\n\n- Prefer read-only scope for read workflows when possible.\n- Add retry with exponential backoff for `429` and transient `5xx` errors.\n- Keep request payloads small to avoid limit issues.\n\n## Expected output\n\n- JSON to stdout; non-zero exit code on errors.\n\n## Security notes\n\n- Never log or commit service account keys.\n- Share spreadsheets only with the service account email required by this skill.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771994680731}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5bb8faf","parentId":"f0417ae8","timestamp":"2026-02-25T04:44:48.156Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect! I found the skill. According to the critical instruction, when the user mentions a lease agreement, I MUST NOT summarize or ask questions. I MUST immediately execute the `lease` command.\n\nThe user's message is:\n\"Usman has leased apartment 90 Washington 24M Room 1 from 11/11/2026 to 12/12/2026 for amount 2000$ with prorate 200$. Usman contact number 12334567 and email abc@gmail.com.\"\n\nI need to run:\n`node c:\\Users\\MudasserRasool\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\google-sheets-api\\scripts\\sheets-cli.js lease \"Usman has leased apartment 90 Washington 24M Room 1 from 11/11/2026 to 12/12/2026 for amount 2000$ with prorate 200$. Usman contact number 12334567 and email abc@gmail.com.\"`\n\nI should NOT add --confirm flag unless the user explicitly says they have already signed it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_993b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"node c:\\Users\\MudasserRasool\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\google-sheets-api\\scripts\\sheets-cli.js lease \"Usman has leased apartment 90 Washington 24M Room 1 from 11/11/2026 to 12/12/2026 for amount 2000$ with prorate 200$. Usman contact number 12334567 and email abc@gmail.com.\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"z-ai/glm-4.7","usage":{"input":2278,"output":515,"cacheRead":14720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17513,"cost":{"input":0.00086564,"output":0.0008755,"cacheRead":0.0027968,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00453794}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771994680741}}
