{"type":"message","id":"af08edaa","parentId":"33acb6ed","timestamp":"2026-02-25T04:45:03.912Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The command failed because there are no Google Sheets credentials configured. The skill requires one of the following:\n- GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY environment variable\n- GOOGLE_SHEETS_CREDENTIALS_JSON environment variable\n- credentials.json file in the skill folder\n\nI need to inform the user about this issue and guide them on how to set up the credentials. According to the SKILL.md, this requires:\n\n1. Create or select a Google Cloud project\n2. Enable the Google Sheets API\n3. Create a service account and download its JSON key\n4. Share target spreadsheets with the service account email\n\nLet me provide clear instructions to the user.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"The Google Sheets integration needs credentials to be configured before I can process the lease agreement. You'll need to set up a service account for Google Sheets API access.\n\nHere's what you need to do:\n\n**1. Create Google Cloud Project & Service Account:**\n   - Go to Google Cloud Console\n   - Create a new project (or use existing)\n   - Enable \"Google Sheets API\"\n   - Create a service account\n   - Download the service account JSON key file\n\n**2. Configure Credentials:**\n   Either:\n   - Set environment variable: `set GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY=path\\to\\your-key.json`\n   - Or save the key file as: `C:\\Users\\MudasserRasool\\.openclaw\\workspace\\skills\\google-sheets-api\\credentials.json`\n\n**3. Share Spreadsheets:**\n   - Share the spreadsheet ID `1RobrLNYSmMUyq53dUcdmj2ePaU2YkagqLqgIgx7M4OU` (your inventory/cleaning sheet)\n   - Share the audit log spreadsheet `1x7Ch_AOuLk6Zht2ef0Q--2K_QueKvcAft-P6d0sx76A`\n   - Grant edit access to the service account email\n\nOnce you've set up the credentials, let me know and I'll process the lease agreement for Usman."}],"api":"openai-completions"